oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Transporting cotton
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a mule-drawn wagon carrying cotton bales down a road in Madison County. An unidentified man steering the wagon is seated on top of the bales. Three unidentified individuals can be seen riding alongside him, one in a car and the others in a wagon.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Mules; Carts & wagons; Cotton; Automobiles; People
